DataElement.preferredName: Medical Image Image Feature Set Image Feature Quantity java.lang.Integer
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any record of a medical imaging event whether physical or electronic.:In image processing, a piece of information which is relevant for solving the computational task related to a certain application, either specific structures in the image itself (e.g., simple structures such as points or edges to more complex structures such as objects) or the result of a general neighborhood operation (feature extractor or feature detector) applied to the image.:A group of things of the same kind that belong together and are so used._In image processing, a piece of information which is relevant for solving the computational task related to a certain application, either specific structures in the image itself (e.g., simple structures such as points or edges to more complex structures such as objects) or the result of a general neighborhood operation (feature extractor or feature detector) applied to the image.:How much there is of something that you can measure; the total amount or number._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
